Section 1:
132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 173
An Act to Exempt Certain Watercraft from Registration
Requirements
Reference to the Committee on Inland Fisheries and Wildlife suggested and ordered
printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative WOOD of Greene.
Cosponsored by Representatives: DRINKWATER of Milford, MASON of Lisbon, THORNE
of Carmel.
Printed on recycled paper
1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 12 MRSA §13056, sub-§2, ¶G, as amended by PL 2013, c. 408, §24, is
3 further amended to read:
4 G. A motorboat used exclusively for racing purposes that displays on its hull in a
5 prominent manner a valid boat number issued by a recognized racing association; and
6 Sec. 2. 12 MRSA §13056, sub-§2, ¶H, as enacted by PL 2013, c. 408, §25, is
7 amended to read:
8 H. A motorboat participating in an event as permitted by section 13061.; and
9 Sec. 3. 12 MRSA §13056, sub-§2, ¶I is enacted to read:
10 I. A canoe, kayak or rowboat that is equipped with a motor having a manufacturer's
11 horsepower rating less than 100 horsepower.
12 SUMMARY
1133 This bill exempts canoes, kayaks and rowboats that are equipped with a motor having
1144 a manufacturer's horsepower rating less than 100 horsepower from boat registration
1155 requirements.
Page 1 - 132LR0502(01)
